title: Speech perception experiment. Earn $1.50 for 15 minutes.

title: Speech perception experiment. Earn $1.50 for 15 minutes.
description: Listen to audio clips and type what you hear. Please only participate if you are a native speaker of English, and at most speak a few words of another language.
Answer.comments: Ah, I see that perhaps the second speaker may have been from Korea.  Honestly, I hear many Korean speakers, and they do not sound so depressed.  That was really throwing me off.  Koreans, in my experience, have a bit of an uptick to their vocal tones, even if some of their syllables drag from time to time.
Answer.guess_accent: The last talker sounds like he may be from India.  Perhaps from an African country, but their English is usually more clipped-sounding.  He spoke in a very draggy way, like he was depressed or something.  The first speaker sounded like he was from India, or perhaps China, or another country in Southeastern Asia, or Malaysia.  (I work for a very diverse university, and hear many accents in the course of my day.)
Answer.language_background_free: I am a native of the US, have never lived outside the US, and do not speak any other language.
